Text.Value: Kled heard it cry. It said 'Auntie Ethel' - and that she was dying.
Mayrina - what are you doing here?
*Sniff.* Kled smells the truth.
Here - a token for your bravery, though it is but small against such a monumental deed.
Were it not for you, this redcap would have been the end of us. Here - a token for your bravery, though it is but small against such a monumental deed.
Is it dead? Please tell Kled that it's dead.

EditorData.AnimationTags: Characters gather to look at the red cap corpse

Text.Value: Urgh. My mouth tastes like mutton - and everything is so itchy.

EditorData.NodeContext: a shudder (talking about being turned into a sheep)

Text.Value: This is the one who dared the depths of a hag lair? It is a pleasure - Mayrina has spoken of you often.
Hah! That's a nice way of saying I'm not such a brat - but I appreciate it.
I didn't do it for you.
Yes - I'm glad you're all safe.
*Sniff.* You smell weird - like death and, and hag magic!
But we drew the ire of Auntie Ethel and she sent this redcap, among other evils, to kill us. Is it true, then? Is the witch dead?
Who are you people?
Thankfully with Ethel gone, no one else will know what it's like to shit pellets.

EditorData.NodeContext: making a joke of her situation

Text.Value: You're bloody welcome.
I came to the city, looking for people like me who'd fallen victim to the hag. Sadly, I found plenty.
As if I would let you leave with empty pockets.
Damn straight - now pay up.
Here - a little thank you for killing Ethel, from me and the little one.
Simply shrug.
Glad to see you in human form again. How was life as a sheep?
Curious. Few who tangle with a hag survive - as we know too well. We're victims of a hag's cruelty and formed this group to research our tormentors.
I was happy to kill Ethel.
Good. I'm only sad I couldn't see it myself.
You've grown up a lot since we last met.
We prefer the term 'survivors', thank you very much.
As am I - it will be a pleasure to sleep with both eyes shut.
Indeed - it killed itself with no hesitation. But why?
By Helm, thank you. We'd been researching hags, and made the mistake of drawing Auntie Ethel's ire.
It killed itself with no hesitation. Why would it do such a thing?
Glad to help.
Gang - meet the hero who rescued me and my little one from Auntie Ethel - and was then kind enough to finish the job.
What a bunch of misfits.
I killed her - she's not coming back.
It was crying - saying Ethel was dying.
Mayrina? Is that you?
Can confirm - that is a dead redcap.
I didn't do this for you.
Nice to meet you.
We were researching hags when Auntie Ethel's redcap found us. Cheers for taking care of the witch - only sad I couldn't see it.
Well, I'll bloody be. Should've known if anyone was going to save the day, it'd be you.
With Ethel gone, maybe I'll finally sleep in peace. Thanks - from me and the little one.
The gang said they'd seen you. Glad you made sure Ethel got what's coming.
I killed her - and she's not coming back.
Could it be? Is our tormentor gone? Is Ethel finally dead?
Don't be shy, gang - she's one of the good ones.
Don't be shy, gang - he's one of the good ones.
Don't be shy, gang - they're one of the good ones.
Dealing with a hag can leave one a touch paranoid - I do not blame you for keeping secrets. Nevertheless, thank you.
That's a dead redcap, all right - ugly bastards.
You hardly expected me to just sit on my backside after you saved me, hm?
Still crabby, I see. Well, you have my gratitude regardless. Thanks - from me and the little one.

Synopsis:
Dialog between survivors gathered around a dead hag spy, Jatlo. Happens when the hag is killed before players have triggered combat with the spy.

Mayrina and Mask of Regret are optional speakers.
